Preheat the #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @baby potatoes{400%grams} into 2cm chunks.

Pop onto a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste} then season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Toss to coat, spread out and roast until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Cut into 2cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(chopped) (or use a #garlic press{}).

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, place a large pan over medium-high heat (no oil).

When hot, add the @Irish beef mince{250%grams} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Break it up with a #spoon{} as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the pepper, garlic and @Mexican style spice mix{1%sachet} to the pan with a drizzle of @?oil{to taste} if needed.

Cook until softened, ~{5-7%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pour the @passata{1%pack} into the pan along with @water{100%ml}.

> Double water quantity for 4p.

Stir in the @beef stock{1%sachet}, bring to the boil then reduce the heat to medium.

Allow to simmer and thicken, stirring occasionally until there is almost no liquid left, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the mixture becomes too dry.

Meanwhile, halve the @avocado{1} and remove the pit. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out into a #bowl{}.

Halve the @lemon{1} and add a squeeze of juice to the bowl with a pinch of salt and pepper.

Mash the avocado with a #fork{}.

Taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice if desired.

Once the sauce in the pan has thickened, season to taste with salt and pepper.

Spoon into an #oven dish{}, top with the roast potato and sprinkle over the @grated cheese{50%grams}.

Place on the top shelf of your oven and bake until the cheese has melted and is golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Dish up spoonfuls of Mexican spiced cheesy beef hash.

Top with freshly made guacamole.

Serve with any remaining lemon cut into wedges.